definitions.definition: ( nautical ) A small flat-bottomed boat with pointed or somewhat pointed ends, used for fishing both offshore and on rivers .

main_definition: ( nautical ) A small flat-bottomed boat with pointed or somewhat pointed ends, used for fishing both offshore and on rivers .

definitions.definition: Any of several different families of large-eyed, silvery , deep-bodied, laterally compressed , and roughly discoid marine fish.

main_definition: Any of several different families of large-eyed, silvery , deep-bodied, laterally compressed , and roughly discoid marine fish.

definitions.definition: A wooden pike or spear about three metres (ten feet ) in length with a flat, leaf-shaped iron spearhead and a bronze butt - spike (called a sauroter ), which was the main weapon of hoplites in Ancient Greece. It was usually not thrown but rather thrust at opponents with one hand.
